erstands who worship the same Now suppose that that place is some other Arab And now suppose that the war is over and that there is a new country created where my father used to live and that that country is called And that in that country Jews from all over the world are And that people whose family left thet country generation ago are recieved and granted full Should I if I decided to go back to my father's land where he was born as or generations of my family were born have the right to go back and ask to be recognized in the same way those who are returning after years Then finally people ask me how I would define a Jew but that is I am not talking about how I would define a Jew but about how people in Zionist organizations and more important in Israel define a How would those who are Zionist define a Jew Eric Perlman Center for Astrophysics and Space Astronomy University of Colorado Boulder AAP